Do you hold a managerial position ?

Maturity
Phase

responses.answerTextAng: Discuss them with my supervisor or team for further guidance.
responses.questionTextAng: When I identify areas for improvement in my work, I:
How often do you suggest new ideas or improvements to your team or organization?
When a problem arises, I actively take steps to solve it rather than waiting for instructions.
I feel confident in making decisions independently when necessary.
I take ownership of my work and responsibilities without being asked.
I consistently set personal goals to enhance my professional growth.
How likely are you to volunteer for tasks outside of your assigned duties?
How comfortable are you with taking on new responsibilities or tasks outside your usual scope?
I seek resources or assistance to complete challenging tasks instead of postponing them.
I take initiative to find solutions when faced with obstacles in my work.
How often do you actively seek opportunities to collaborate with colleagues from different departments or teams?
When working on a team project, I contribute my skills and knowledge to achieve collective goals.
I make an effort to understand the perspectives and ideas of my colleagues.
I openly share information and updates with my team to ensure everyone is aligned.
I value and respect input from all team members, even if it differs from my own perspective.
When conflicts arise within the team, I actively work to resolve them constructively.
I encourage collaboration and actively involve others in decision-making processes.
How comfortable are you sharing ideas during team discussions or meetings?
I frequently acknowledge and appreciate the contributions of others.
I make an effort to build strong working relationships with colleagues.

responses.answerTextAng: Always act on it to improve.
responses.questionTextAng: When receiving constructive feedback, I:
How often do you actively seek feedback from your supervisors or colleagues to enhance your performance?
I view feedback as an opportunity for growth and development.
I remain open-minded when receiving suggestions for improvement.
When I disagree with feedback, I address it professionally and respectfully.
I proactively follow up with colleagues or supervisors to clarify feedback when needed.
How comfortable are you providing feedback to others in a constructive manner?
I regularly review past feedback to ensure I have addressed it effectively.
I appreciate receiving recognition for work well done.
I encourage a culture of feedback within my team or department.
I am comfortable adjusting my approach when a project's goals or requirements change.
How quickly do you adapt to changes in processes or procedures?
I see change as an opportunity for growth rather than a challenge to overcome.
When priorities shift unexpectedly, I stay focused and productive.
I can quickly learn and apply new skills or knowledge as needed.
How comfortable are you working in an unpredictable or fast-changing environment?
I remain positive and calm under pressure or during major changes.
I actively seek out ways to help my team adapt to changes.
I enjoy taking on new challenges, even if they require me to step outside of my comfort zone.
I seek feedback on how I handle change to improve my adaptability in the future.
I consistently look for ways to improve my own performance and efficiency at work.
How often do you identify areas within the organization that could benefit from improvement?
I am willing to invest time in learning new methods, tools, or processes to enhance my work.
When I make a mistake, I focus on learning from it to prevent it from happening again.
I encourage others to share innovative ideas to improve processes or solve problems.
I keep myself updated with the latest developments and trends in my field.
How frequently do you suggest new ways to increase efficiency or productivity in your role?
I seek opportunities to learn from experienced colleagues or industry experts.
I am committed to achieving excellence in all aspects of my work.
How likely are you to adopt new technologies or tools to improve work quality?

Which company are working for (Optional) ?
In which sector/industry do you evolve ?
Enter your email here (if you want us to share the results with you) - it's optional
Maturity
Phase

responses.answerTextAng: Discuss them with my supervisor or team for further guidance.
responses.questionTextAng: When I identify areas for improvement in my work, I:
How often do you suggest new ideas or improvements to your team or organization?
When a problem arises, I actively take steps to solve it rather than waiting for instructions.
I feel confident in making decisions independently when necessary.
I take ownership of my work and responsibilities without being asked.
I consistently set personal goals to enhance my professional growth.
How likely are you to volunteer for tasks outside of your assigned duties?
How comfortable are you with taking on new responsibilities or tasks outside your usual scope?
I seek resources or assistance to complete challenging tasks instead of postponing them.
I take initiative to find solutions when faced with obstacles in my work.
How often do you actively seek opportunities to collaborate with colleagues from different departments or teams?
When working on a team project, I contribute my skills and knowledge to achieve collective goals.
I make an effort to understand the perspectives and ideas of my colleagues.
I openly share information and updates with my team to ensure everyone is aligned.
I value and respect input from all team members, even if it differs from my own perspective.
When conflicts arise within the team, I actively work to resolve them constructively.
I encourage collaboration and actively involve others in decision-making processes.
How comfortable are you sharing ideas during team discussions or meetings?
I frequently acknowledge and appreciate the contributions of others.
I make an effort to build strong working relationships with colleagues.

responses.answerTextAng: Always act on it to improve.
responses.questionTextAng: When receiving constructive feedback, I:
How often do you actively seek feedback from your supervisors or colleagues to enhance your performance?
I view feedback as an opportunity for growth and development.
I remain open-minded when receiving suggestions for improvement.
When I disagree with feedback, I address it professionally and respectfully.
I proactively follow up with colleagues or supervisors to clarify feedback when needed.
How comfortable are you providing feedback to others in a constructive manner?
I regularly review past feedback to ensure I have addressed it effectively.
I appreciate receiving recognition for work well done.
I encourage a culture of feedback within my team or department.
I am comfortable adjusting my approach when a project's goals or requirements change.
How quickly do you adapt to changes in processes or procedures?
I see change as an opportunity for growth rather than a challenge to overcome.
When priorities shift unexpectedly, I stay focused and productive.
I can quickly learn and apply new skills or knowledge as needed.
How comfortable are you working in an unpredictable or fast-changing environment?
I remain positive and calm under pressure or during major changes.
I actively seek out ways to help my team adapt to changes.
I enjoy taking on new challenges, even if they require me to step outside of my comfort zone.
I seek feedback on how I handle change to improve my adaptability in the future.
I consistently look for ways to improve my own performance and efficiency at work.
How often do you identify areas within the organization that could benefit from improvement?
I am willing to invest time in learning new methods, tools, or processes to enhance my work.
When I make a mistake, I focus on learning from it to prevent it from happening again.
I encourage others to share innovative ideas to improve processes or solve problems.
I keep myself updated with the latest developments and trends in my field.
How frequently do you suggest new ways to increase efficiency or productivity in your role?
I seek opportunities to learn from experienced colleagues or industry experts.
I am committed to achieving excellence in all aspects of my work.
How likely are you to adopt new technologies or tools to improve work quality?

categoryScores.categoryAng: Openness to feedback: Receptiveness to Input
Citing continuous improvement: striving for excellence
